<item>
  <title>[English] Creating a New Theme</title>
  <link>http://blog.codepeak.cn/english-preview/</link>
  <pubDate>Thu, 31 Aug 2017 15:43:48 &#43;0800</pubDate>
  <author>作者</author>
  <guid>http://blog.codepeak.cn/english-preview/</guid>
  <description><![CDATA[Introduction This tutorial will show you how to create a simple theme in Hugo. I assume that you are familiar with HTML, the bash command line, and that you are comfortable using Markdown to format content. I&rsquo;ll explain how Hugo uses templates and how you can organize your templates to create a theme. I won&rsquo;t cover using CSS to style your theme.
We&rsquo;ll start with creating a new site with a very basic template.]]></description>
</item>
